{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e2f60abc-099e-4b03-91e1-99b8e1ca7949","content":"With MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9, you can use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` and combine it with `[TestInitialize]` for async setup. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Sync init + TestContext injection via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService(); // sync setup\n    }\n\n    // Async init via [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Initialized\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Test1()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — receives `TestContext` and handles synchronous setup (runs once per test instance).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — use for `async Task` setup that runs before each test.\n- No need for `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property — constructor injection replaces it.\n- The constructor runs *before* `[TestInitialize]`, so put dependency ordering accordingly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8d18600-d72a-4692-bb5c-72ce1a12adb0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended approach is:\n1. Use constructor injection to receive `TestContext`\n2. Use `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous setup (or put sync init in the constructor)\n3. Use `[TestInitialize]` with `async Task` for asynchronous setup\n\nActually, let me be more precise. In MSTest v3.8+, `TestContext` can be injected via constructor. \n\nSo the pattern is straightforward: put your synchronous initialization in the constructor where you receive the injected `TestContext`, and use `[TestInitialize]` methods for any async setup work.","outputTokens":503,"requestId":"A032:2950B:3F3DDC0:438BE46:6A034CD6"},"id":"4ff56534-eec4-462b-9d6e-ac633c7dbbf2","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:53:06.994Z","parentId":"de3bf140-680a-4785-96d9-52e6c6fbdfeb"}
